<h1>Mohit Pawar</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://mohitpawar.com/now/">mohitpawar.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
New Delhi

India
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Entrepreneur ( Founder, MasterClass - <a href="http://mclass.co/">http://mclass.co/</a> ). Most of my projects are listed here: <a href="http://www.metadoor.in/">http://www.metadoor.in/</a>
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I start projects, write words (and books) and help others.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I start new projects to make sure that I don't get too comfortable feeling that I know everything. I write to share ideas with the world and find clarity. I help others because that is the right thing to do.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
That we need to increase the size of our box. It takes same time and almost same energy to work on a small idea as it takes to work on an idea that can touch a million or billion lives.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
E-Myth Revisited by Michael Gerber
</p>

